    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix CIMI AT command response handling for test commands\n\n### Summary\nThe `_at_response_encode_cimi()` function was not properly handling AT command test requests (AT+CIMI=?), causing unexpected behavior when the function was called with `AT_COMMAND_TST` type. This fix adds proper handling for test commands while maintaining backward compatibility.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/API/USER/at_response.c`: Modified `_at_response_encode_cimi()` to handle both `AT_COMMAND_ACT` and `AT_COMMAND_TST` types\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/API/USER/at_response.c`: Also updated CGSN, CGMI, CGMM, and CGMR functions for consistency\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen calling `_at_response_encode_cimi()` with `data->type == AT_COMMAND_TST`, the function would previously return 0 bytes encoded, resulting in no response being generated. With this fix, test commands now properly return `+CIMI: ()\\r\\n` format responses as expected according to 3GPP TS 27.007 specification.\n\nThe same issue affected the other informational AT commands (CGSN, CGMI, CGMM, CGMR) which also only handled action commands but not test commands. These have been updated for consistency.\n\n"
}